## Purpose

Memory mode selects whether durable project knowledge has a home that OUTLIVES the unit of work.

It is set in `PIPELINE-CONFIG.json`:

```json
{
    "workflow": {
        "memory_mode": "project_scoped"
    }
}
```

Two values: `project_scoped` and `task_scoped`.

This axis decides which memory artifacts are active. In `project_scoped` mode the full memory model applies, including a project-level decision log and context capsules that accrete across the whole project. In `task_scoped` mode there is no project-owned durable home, so durable knowledge folds into the unit-of-work active state and is archived with that unit.

Memory mode is orthogonal to `branch_mode`: branch mode decides WHERE active working memory physically lives during work, memory mode decides WHETHER there is a durable home that survives the unit of work.
